OL,3,CMedicines regulator to approve
OL,4,CAlzheimer's drug shown to slow disease
OL,6,FThe EMA said the benefits of lecanemab
OL,7,Fdid not counterbalance the risk of
OL,8,Fpeople suffering serious side-effects,
OL,9,Fsuch as bleeding and swelling in the
OL,10,Fbrain.
OL,12,FAdditionally, it said the effects of
OL,13,Fthe drug on delaying cognitive decline
OL,14,Fwere small.
OL,16,FA similar drug called donanemab, which
OL,17,Fis developed by Eli Lilly, is also
OL,18,Fbeing assessed for approval in the UK
OL,19,Fby medicine regulators.
